That was incredible.

692
00:50:24,780 --> 00:50:26,130
你们是舞蹈演员吗？
You dance for a living?

693
00:50:26,210 --> 00:50:27,870
哦 不 不
No. Oh, no. I...

694
00:50:27,950 --> 00:50:29,870
-不 不是的 -你做什么的？
-No, I do not, sir. -What do you do for a living?

695
00:50:29,960 --> 00:50:31,850
哎呦 我好像不小心搞坏了
Oh, no, I think I... Did I... I didn't break it, did I?

696
00:50:31,870 --> 00:50:34,070
这个好像坏了
I think he broke it.

697
00:50:35,310 --> 00:50:36,840
去喷泉吧
Let's hit the pond.

698
00:50:36,920 --> 00:50:39,170
那儿没停车位
We'll never find parking by the Common.

699
00:50:39,530 --> 00:50:40,570
那也要停
We will today.

700
00:50:41,920 --> 00:50:46,190
今天 就像魔术一样
Today...is magic.

701
00:50:50,670 --> 00:50:54,470
你们在哪练的这身舞功？
Where did you learn to dance like that?

702
00:51:00,160 --> 00:51:02,400
别 别 别 那是你赚的
Oh, no, no, no, that's yours.

703
00:51:02,420 --> 00:51:04,010
不 有福同享
Nope, we split it even.

704
00:51:04,030 --> 00:51:08,470
要我自己敲 一天也赚不了这么多
By myself, I wouldn't have made half as much if I drummed till midnight.

705
00:51:17,440 --> 00:51:18,610
你没事吧？
You okay?

706
00:51:20,660 --> 00:51:22,340
还好
Yeah.

707
00:51:23,920 --> 00:51:26,690
就是有点头疼
Yeah. Just one of my headaches.

708
00:51:28,360 --> 00:51:30,820
不了 不了 真用不着 你留着吧
Oh, no, no, no. Come on. I don't need it. You keep it.

709
00:51:30,840 --> 00:51:33,260
来吧 老兄 你应得的
Come on, man, you earned it.

710
00:51:33,280 --> 00:51:40,000
拿去吃顿饭 转手送人也行 但这钱我偏要交给你
Buy yourself dinner. Give it away. But I'm handing it to you.

711
00:51:42,640 --> 00:51:44,400
你们干这行都能当职业了
You could do this for a living, you know?

712
00:51:44,420 --> 00:51:46,360
我可不敢这么说
I don't know about that.

713
00:51:46,380 --> 00:51:50,300
我真觉得靠街头表演 我们能红 能赚大钱
I really think we could busk our way to fame and fortune.

714
00:51:52,780 --> 00:51:56,830
你怎么会停在我面前？
What made you stop in front of me?

715
00:51:58,040 --> 00:52:01,620
又为什么突然跳起舞？
Why did you start moving?

716
00:52:01,900 --> 00:52:08,470
他本可说鼓点让他想起他那不成气候的追旧青年乐队
He could say it was because he was thinking about his old half-assed band, The Retros,

717
00:52:08,490 --> 00:52:14,370
他还喜欢跟着节奏跳舞
and how he liked to dance across the stage during instrumental breaks.

718
00:52:14,410 --> 00:52:16,160
但他没这么说
But that's not it.

719
00:52:19,590 --> 00:52:21,760
我也说不清
I don't know.

720
00:52:24,500 --> 00:52:25,960
泰勒 该走了
Taylor, we gotta roll,

721
00:52:25,980 --> 00:52:29,450
不然你赚的钱都得交罚单了
or you're gonna end up spending your take on my parking ticket.

722
00:52:29,990 --> 00:52:33,060
你们不考虑转行跳舞吗？
So, you guys don't want a career change?

723
00:52:33,080 --> 00:52:34,970
转行？
Career change? How... I mean...

724
00:52:34,990 --> 00:52:37,280
我们肯定能闯出名堂
We'll make a name for ourselves.

725
00:52:38,390 --> 00:52:40,980
别急着走 先进来一下
You got to get in here before you go.

726
00:52:41,000 --> 00:52:43,070
-来个大团抱！ -哦 哦 好
-Group hug. -Oh, oh, okay.

727
00:52:43,090 --> 00:52:44,400
-大团抱！ -来
-Group hug. -Okay.

728
00:52:44,480 --> 00:52:45,980
快 快 快
Go.

729
00:52:46,000 --> 00:52:47,600
来 来
Come on.

730
00:52:53,880 --> 00:52:55,860
街头艺人万岁
Buskers forever.

731
00:52:55,880 --> 00:52:57,430
好了 好了
Yeah. Buskers forever.

732
00:52:57,450 --> 00:53:00,690
得赶在贴罚单前抓紧走
We gotta roll before the meter maid shows up.

733
00:53:05,940 --> 00:53:07,610
真替你难过
I'm so sorry.

734
00:53:08,070 --> 00:53:09,310
真倒霉
That sucks.

735
00:53:09,330 --> 00:53:11,290
这确实倒霉
It does suck.

736
00:53:11,940 --> 00:53:13,880
我真觉得他人还不错
I thought he was a nice guy.

737
00:53:13,900 --> 00:53:17,420
床上功夫也到位 我们在一起挺开心的
He was a pretty good lover, and we had fun and all that.

738
00:53:17,690 --> 00:53:22,370
我回去得找下我们跳舞的视频 估计会上热搜
If I can find a video of us dancing, which I'm gonna look because I bet we go viral,

739
00:53:22,390 --> 00:53:29,940
然后转发给他 再附句“这就是你错过的缘分”
I'm gonna send it to him with a text, a text that says, "This is what you're missing."

740
00:53:36,580 --> 00:53:38,680
你会没事的
You're gonna be fine.

741
00:53:40,060 --> 00:53:43,710
我不是全都懂 可这件事我很清楚
I don't know a lot, but I know that much.

742
00:53:45,410 --> 00:53:52,640
光辉就在你前面 往前迈一步乌云就消散
You got a bright sunbeam in front of you, and you're gonna step right into it, I can tell.

743
00:53:53,070 --> 00:53:54,240
但现在
But yeah.

744
00:53:56,380 --> 00:53:59,350
真倒霉 没啥好说的
It sucks. Not much else to say.

745
00:54:01,640 --> 00:54:06,020
一切都完了 我们也只剩下句真倒霉
Everything goes down the drain, and all we can say is, "That sucks."

746
00:54:06,050 --> 00:54:07,220
对
Yeah.

747
00:54:08,040 --> 00:54:11,940
说不定谁都躲不掉这劫
Maybe we're going down the drain too.

748
00:54:11,960 --> 00:54:13,640
说不定
Maybe.

749
00:54:15,660 --> 00:54:17,420
我走这条路
I'm this way.

750
00:54:19,580 --> 00:54:22,390
我往那边走
Uh, I'm that way.

751
00:54:27,240 --> 00:54:29,620
多谢你陪我跳舞
Thank you for the dance.

752
00:55:24,030 --> 00:55:27,360
当他走过泰勒摆鼓的地方
As he passes the place where Taylor set up her drums,

753
00:55:27,380 --> 00:55:31,430
那两个问题又冒了出来
those two questions recur.

754
00:55:32,300 --> 00:55:36,280
为什么要停下脚步听？
Why did he stop to listen?

755
00:55:36,300 --> 00:55:41,270
又为什么要跳起舞？
And why did he start to dance?

756
00:55:42,050 --> 00:55:45,130
他自己也想不通
He doesn't know.

757
00:55:45,310 --> 00:55:51,210
有答案能让这回忆更动人吗？
And would answers make a good thing better?

758
00:55:51,230 --> 00:55:54,910
后来 他走路都成问题
Later, he'll lose the ability to walk,

759
00:55:54,930 --> 00:55:59,740
和那个小老妹跳舞成了个传说
never mind dancing with little sister on the promenade.

760
00:55:59,760 --> 00:56:04,140
再后来 他咀嚼都成了难题
Later, he'll lose the ability to chew food.

761
00:56:04,160 --> 00:56:08,190
再后来 他记不住妻子的名字
Later, he'll forget his wife's name.

762
00:56:08,210 --> 00:56:14,150
到最后 他分不清白日黑夜
Later, he'll lose his grip on the difference between waking and sleeping

763
00:56:14,170 --> 00:56:23,160
陷入一种让人质疑生命意义的巨大痛苦中
and enter a land of pain so great he will wonder why God made the world.

764
00:56:23,180 --> 00:56:30,080
但有时 他还会记得当初把公文包一丢
What he will remember, occasionally, is how he stopped and dropped his briefcase

765
00:56:30,100 --> 00:56:34,690
跟着鼓点起舞的感觉
and began to move his hips to the beat of the drums.

766
00:56:34,710 --> 00:56:40,830
他会觉得 这就是上帝让世界存在的意义
And he will think that is why God made the world.

767
00:56:40,850 --> 00:56:42,930
仅此而已
Just that.

768
00:56:58,080 --> 00:56:59,390
{\an8}第一幕

769
00:56:59,390 --> 00:57:04,160
{\an8}第一幕
我包罗万象

770
00:57:06,050 --> 00:57:09,940
查克一直盼着能有个小妹妹
Chuck was looking forward to having a baby sister.

771
00:57:09,960 --> 00:57:13,950
更盼着父母能赶紧回来
Of course, he was also looking forward to having parents,

772
00:57:13,970 --> 00:57:22,070
谁料95号高架上结的冰让一切化为泡影
but none of that worked out thanks to a patch 95 of well-hidden ice on an I-95 overpass.

773
00:57:23,590 --> 00:57:26,130
事发时查克没在车上
Chuck wasn't in the car when it happened

774
00:57:26,150 --> 00:57:28,920
他父母去享受二人世界
because his parents were having a dinner date

775
00:57:28,940 --> 00:57:32,360
那天晚上他爷爷奶奶带他
and he was being babysat by his grandparents,

776
00:57:32,380 --> 00:57:36,270
他那会儿还叫他们阿爷阿奶
who, at the time, he was still calling Zaydee and Bubbie.

777
00:57:32,380 --> 00:57:37,860
{\an9}【Zaydee和Bubbie是东欧犹太移民常用的祖父母称呼】

778
00:57:36,290 --> 00:57:37,840
他那时七岁了
He was seven years old.

779
00:57:37,860 --> 00:57:39,920
真赞喔
Excellent job.

780
00:57:40,210 --> 00:57:46,070
一年半载 屋子里全是悲伤
For a year and a half, it was a house of unadulterated sadness.

781
00:57:46,090 --> 00:57:50,990
对阿尔比和莎拉·克兰兹来说 不只是儿子和儿媳没了
Albie and Sarah Krantz had not only lost their son and daughter-in-law...

782
00:57:51,010 --> 00:57:52,470
咋不吃饭了？
Why're you not eating?

783
00:57:52,490 --> 00:57:57,070
那本该三个月后出生的孙女也没了
...they had lost the granddaughter who would've been born just three months later.

784
00:57:57,090 --> 00:57:58,770
咋回事儿？
What's going on?

785
00:57:58,790 --> 00:58:01,080
名字都选好了...
The name had already been picked out...

786
00:58:01,100 --> 00:58:03,520
-她叫艾雨莎 -艾雨莎
-Her name is Alyssa. -...Alyssa.

787
00:58:03,540 --> 00:58:07,060
查克说那名字听着像下雨时
When Chuck said that sounded to him like rain,

788
00:58:07,060 --> 00:58:11,130
他妈哭笑不得
his mother had laughed and cried at the same time.

789
00:58:11,150 --> 00:58:14,430
他永远忘不了那表情
He never forgot that.

790
00:58:14,850 --> 00:58:19,800
阿尔比靠两件事来排解悲伤
Albie processed his grief by turning to his two absolutes,

791
00:58:19,820 --> 00:58:23,190
算账和喝酒
numbers and alcohol.

792
00:58:23,210 --> 00:58:28,110
但对莎拉来说 一切却都失去了滋味
Sarah, though, could find no joy in her usual pleasures.

793
00:58:28,130 --> 00:58:32,980
曾让她陶醉的音乐 艺术和美食
She loved the flavors of life, music, art, and food,

794
00:58:33,000 --> 00:58:38,500
如今都索然无味
but now, found the world quiet and gray and flavorless.

795
00:58:40,360 --> 00:58:44,860
随着时间流逝 家里又慢慢有了些温暖
Some of the good feelings came back into the house with time.

796
00:58:44,880 --> 00:58:48,480
事故后全靠外卖度日
There were a lot of takeout meals after the accident,

797
00:58:48,500 --> 00:58:53,740
但查克快十岁那年 他奶奶又重新下厨
but around the time Chuck turned 10, his grandma started cooking again.

798
00:58:53,760 --> 00:58:57,590
她做饭时爱放摇滚乐
She liked rock-and-roll while she was cooking.

799
00:58:57,610 --> 00:59:05,600
查克肯定觉得太潮了 可她显然乐在其中
Music Chuck would've thought much too young for her, but which she clearly enjoyed.

800
00:59:22,230 --> 00:59:27,440
来吧 小老弟 来跳舞吧
Come on, little brother, let's dance.

801
00:59:57,580 --> 00:59:58,790
{\an8}《西区故事》

802
01:00:01,240 --> 01:00:02,110
{\an8}《雨中曲》

803
01:00:03,600 --> 01:00:04,730
{\an8}《歌厅》

804
01:00:07,840 --> 01:00:08,980
{\an8}《爵士春秋》

805
01:00:13,390 --> 01:00:15,230
{\an8}《封面女郎》

806
01:00:18,210 --> 01:00:22,510
{\an9}【电影《封面女郎》(1944)】

807
01:00:22,540 --> 01:00:27,380
小宝 你有本事学会 你天生是跳舞的料
You could learn those moves, kiddo. You're a natural.

808
01:00:27,400 --> 01:00:28,790
你在哪学的？
Wh-Where did you learn?

809
01:00:28,810 --> 01:00:30,640
高中
High school.

810
01:00:31,070 --> 01:00:34,320
你上高中的时候是什么样的？
What were you like in high school?

811
01:00:34,340 --> 01:00:36,670
我可是个小辣妹
I was a kusit.

812
01:00:34,340 --> 01:00:36,665
{\an9}【Kusit为希伯来语】

813
01:00:36,690 --> 01:00:39,210
千万别把我这话告诉你阿爷哦
But don't you tell your Zaydee I said that.

814
01:00:39,240 --> 01:00:42,090
他是个老古董
He's old school, that one.

815
01:00:43,570 --> 01:00:46,320
查克守口如瓶
Chuck never told.

816
01:00:46,580 --> 01:00:50,870
他把爷爷奶奶家处处都当自己家
His grandparents' house became every inch his home

817
01:00:50,890 --> 01:00:56,370
除了塔尖阁楼
with one exception. the cupola on the roof.

818
01:00:57,890 --> 01:01:01,930
查克被严令禁止进那阁楼
Chuck was forbidden to go into the cupola.

819
01:01:01,930 --> 01:01:08,360
那是他爷爷的一条铁律 不容置疑
That was his grandfather's rule, and it was absolute, emphatic.

820
01:01:08,380 --> 01:01:11,750
他爷爷阿尔比做事宽容
Albie wasn't a stern man in other matters.

821
01:01:11,770 --> 01:01:15,060
平时人挺温和的
He was downright gentle in most respects.

822
01:01:15,080 --> 01:01:19,540
偏偏在这事上绝不讲情面
But on this point, he was rigid.

823
01:01:20,290 --> 01:01:24,230
查克可不止问过一次
Chuck asked about it, of course, and more than once.

824
01:01:24,260 --> 01:01:28,240
那上头有什么？从高高的窗户能看到啥？
What was up there? What could you see from the high window?

825
01:01:28,260 --> 01:01:33,310
最重要的是 为啥老是锁着？
And the big question, why was the room locked?

826
01:01:33,490 --> 01:01:34,370
他奶奶说...
Grandma said...

827
01:01:34,370 --> 01:01:36,880
楼上地板不结实 一踩就会坍下去
Because the floor isn't safe and you might go right through it.

828
01:01:36,910 --> 01:01:37,820
他爷爷说...
Grandpa said...

829
01:01:37,820 --> 01:01:41,080
由于那烂地板 屋子里空无一物
There's nothing up there because of that rotten floor.

830
01:01:41,080 --> 01:01:44,960
你往窗外瞅 也就只能看到商场
And the only thing you can see through the windows is the shopping center.

831
01:01:44,980 --> 01:01:50,390
他一直这么说 直到查克十一岁生日前一晚
He said that until, one night, just before Chuck's 11th birthday,

832
01:01:50,420 --> 01:01:54,170
他才吐出部分实情
when he told at least part of the truth.

833
