And not pretend Victorian either. It was built in 1885.

859
01:03:34,390 --> 01:03:37,420
后来翻新过大概六次吧
It's been remodeled half a dozen times since.

860
01:03:37,440 --> 01:03:42,340
可那阁楼一直保留至今
But that cupola was there from the start.

861
01:03:42,360 --> 01:03:44,860
我七十年代初搬来
Been here since '71.

862
01:03:44,880 --> 01:03:50,310
搬来至今 我上那阁楼都没到六次
And in all those years, I haven't been up to that damn cupola half a dozen times.

863
01:03:50,330 --> 01:03:52,950
因为地板烂了？
'Cause the floor is rotted?

864
01:03:53,760 --> 01:03:56,820
因为闹鬼
'Cause it's full of ghosts.

865
01:03:57,240 --> 01:04:00,490
{\an7}...发生在12月31日的晚上10点30分
...around 10:30 p.m. on December 31st.

866
01:04:00,940 --> 01:04:03,270
-还记得圣诞述异那个故事吗？ -嗯
-Y-You remember Scrooge? -Yeah.

867
01:04:03,290 --> 01:04:04,950
那部叫做《圣诞欢歌》的电影？
That Scrooge movie we watched?

868
01:04:04,970 --> 01:04:06,270
记得
I remember.

869
01:04:06,290 --> 01:04:09,930
你觉得那算鬼故事吗？
Do you think of that as a ghost story?

870
01:04:09,950 --> 01:04:11,630
算吧
I-I-I guess so.

871
01:04:11,650 --> 01:04:15,340
有人说那是鬼故事
Heard someone say it was a ghost story.

872
01:04:16,870 --> 01:04:22,000
他吓的说“圣诞节未卜先知”
Christmas Yet to Come.

873
01:04:19,740 --> 01:04:24,620
{\an7}晚上11点59分20秒...
11:59:20, evening, last day of the...

874
01:04:24,700 --> 01:04:28,860
杰弗里家那男孩一个月后就没了
Jefferies boy was a month later.

875
01:04:28,880 --> 01:04:39,740
亨利·彼得森拖得久些 等了四五年
Henry Peterson, that took longer. Four...maybe five years on.

876
01:04:39,760 --> 01:04:47,520
到那时 阁楼里看到的 我几乎忘得精光
And by then...I almost forgot what I saw up there.

877
01:04:47,550 --> 01:04:50,400
几乎
Almost.

878
01:04:51,930 --> 01:04:56,630
我说过再也不上去
Said I'd never go back up there after that.

879
01:04:56,650 --> 01:05:03,120
真不想上去 要不是为了莎拉
And I wish I hadn't because of Sarah.

880
01:05:03,520 --> 01:05:08,510
为了你的阿奶 小查
Because of your Bubbie, Chucky.

881
01:05:08,530 --> 01:05:12,430
最疼你的阿奶
Your sweet Bubbie.

882
01:05:12,450 --> 01:05:15,340
都是面包
And the bread.

883
01:05:15,360 --> 01:05:19,940
{\an7}我们听说过的所有人...
Every person we've ever heard of, somewhere in there...

884
01:05:20,020 --> 01:05:23,880
这就是等待 小查
It's the waiting, Chucko.

885
01:05:24,110 --> 01:05:27,110
这是最难熬的
That's the hard part.

886
01:05:25,890 --> 01:05:35,160
{\an7}所有历史书上的事 都只发生在这本日历最后10秒钟里
Everything in the history books happened here in the last 10 seconds of the cosmic calendar.

887
01:05:34,180 --> 01:05:37,510
呜 外面真冷
Ooh! It's getting cold out there.

888
01:05:37,530 --> 01:05:41,160
维拉向大家问好 还谢我煲的汤
Vera says hi. She says thanks for the soup.

889
01:05:41,180 --> 01:05:44,280
她把八卦全抖给我 抖得可带劲了
She laid the gossip on me, laid it good.

890
01:05:44,300 --> 01:05:47,350
当然 要不然咱咋离不开她呢
Of course...That's why we have a Vera, isn't it?

891
01:05:47,370 --> 01:05:49,380
有什么新鲜事吗？
So, what's the latest?

892
01:05:49,400 --> 01:05:54,730
知道吗 凯伦和马蒂在搞婚姻咨询
Well, I don't know if you've heard, but Trish is saying Karen and Matty are in therapy.

893
01:05:54,750 --> 01:06:00,970
-搞什么？ -阿爷 亨利·彼得森到底是谁？
-Again. -Who's Henry Peterson, Zaydee?

894
01:05:57,140 --> 01:06:03,000
{\an7}...珍惜我们的宇宙 不要辜负这150亿年
...the universe that made us or we can squander our 15 billion-year heritage.

895
01:06:03,020 --> 01:06:05,080
再买点煎饼粉
And get some pancake mix.

896
01:06:05,110 --> 01:06:07,770
要黄盒的 别买橙盒的 都记住了吗？
Yellow box, not the orange box. You got all that?

897
01:06:07,800 --> 01:06:09,180
记住了
I got it.

898
01:06:09,200 --> 01:06:11,960
-要我写下来吗？ -我记得住
-Do you need me to write it down? -I got it.

899
01:06:11,980 --> 01:06:15,300
别开车 走路去能醒醒酒
Don't you think about driving. The walk will sober you up.

900
01:06:15,330 --> 01:06:17,780
好 好 好
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

901
01:06:34,740 --> 01:06:37,470
他去便利店了 一会儿就回来
He'll be back with some groceries.

902
01:06:37,490 --> 01:06:43,340
要不今晚一起烤棉花糖？
Then, how about tonight, we do some s'mores in the fireplace?

903
01:06:43,360 --> 01:06:44,570
随便
Yeah.

904
01:06:44,600 --> 01:06:47,010
好吧
Yeah.

905
01:06:47,370 --> 01:06:51,050
他是不是跟你说闹鬼的事了？
Was he blabbing to you about his ghosts?

906
01:06:51,080 --> 01:06:54,550
阁楼里闹鬼的事？
The ones that live in the cupola?

907
01:06:54,900 --> 01:06:56,490
是呀
Yeah.

908
01:06:56,640 --> 01:06:59,700
是真的吗？
Well, are there?

909
01:07:00,070 --> 01:07:02,400
你说呢？
What do you think?

910
01:07:02,420 --> 01:07:05,060
别太信你阿爷
I wouldn't pay too much attention to Zaydee.

911
01:07:05,080 --> 01:07:11,600
他人不错 就是有时喝得太多
He's a good man. But, sometimes, well, sometimes, he drinks too much.

912
01:07:11,630 --> 01:07:14,770
喝多了就会天马行空 你懂他那一套
Then he rides his hobby horses. I'm sure you know what I'm talking about.

913
01:07:14,800 --> 01:07:18,730
杰弗里家男孩是谁？
Who was the Jefferies boy?

914
01:07:21,400 --> 01:07:26,110
好吧 小宝 那是件让人心酸的事
Well...that was a very sad thing, kiddo.

915
01:07:26,370 --> 01:07:28,780
他住旁边那巷子
He lived on the next block over,

916
01:07:28,800 --> 01:07:34,310
追球追到马路上结果被车撞了
and he got hit by a car when he chased a ball into the street.

917
01:07:34,330 --> 01:07:37,810
那是很久前的事儿了
It happened a long time ago.

918
01:07:38,680 --> 01:07:45,800
要是你爷爷说他提前见过那一幕 他并没有
And if your grandpa says he saw it before it happened, he's mistaken.

919
01:07:47,380 --> 01:07:51,800
那只是他酒后乱说
He just drinks too much.

920
01:08:00,610 --> 01:08:05,290
要不我帮你送到史坦利奶奶那儿？
You know, I could take those to Mrs. Stanley if you want.

921
01:08:05,310 --> 01:08:09,900
哎呀 你真贴心 维拉看到你肯定特开心
Oh, that's very thoughtful of you. I bet Vera'd love that.

922
01:08:11,890 --> 01:08:13,480
简直绝了
Just wonderful.

923
01:08:13,500 --> 01:08:15,510
你奶奶真是个烘焙大师
Your, your grandmother is an artist.

924
01:08:15,540 --> 01:08:18,310
谢谢你带来 你主动要来送的吧？
Thank you for bringing them over. Was that your idea?

925
01:08:18,330 --> 01:08:20,050
-说实话哦 -是的
-Be honest. -It was.

926
01:08:20,070 --> 01:08:22,700
要喝茶吗？
Well, can I make you a cup of tea?

927
01:08:22,720 --> 01:08:27,390
其实我不喝茶 有杯牛奶就完美了
Um, I don't drink tea, but, um, I wouldn't mind a glass of milk.

928
01:08:28,670 --> 01:08:31,100
你奶奶真是个大好人
Well, your grandmother's a saint.

929
01:08:31,130 --> 01:08:32,470
你爷爷呢？
And what about your granddad?

930
01:08:32,470 --> 01:08:34,650
他背上那东西去检查了吗？
Did he have that thing on his back looked at?

931
01:08:34,680 --> 01:08:37,150
嗯 医生拿掉了 还做了化验
Yeah, the, the doctor took it off and had it tested.

932
01:08:37,170 --> 01:08:38,850
全告诉我
Tell me everything.

933
01:08:38,870 --> 01:08:41,550
不是坏的那种
It wasn't one of the bad ones.

934
01:08:41,570 --> 01:08:43,290
谢天谢地
Thank God for that.

935
01:08:43,310 --> 01:08:44,780
嗯
Yeah.

936
01:08:45,880 --> 01:08:52,600
他跟奶奶聊那个叫亨利·彼得森的人
He, um, he was talking to Grandma about someone named Henry Peterson.

937
01:08:52,620 --> 01:08:53,910
太惨了
So awful.

938
01:08:53,930 --> 01:08:57,350
亨利跟你爷爷一样是管账的
You know, Henry was a bookkeeper, just like your granddad.

939
01:08:57,370 --> 01:09:00,750
还接了镇上你阿爷扛不下的活儿...
He did a lot of the other businesses in town. The ones that your Zaydee didn't do...

940
01:09:00,780 --> 01:09:03,170
到底怎么回事？
How did it happen?

941
01:09:04,690 --> 01:09:06,750
这种事你还是别听了
I don't think you want to hear about that stuff.

942
01:09:06,770 --> 01:09:11,550
呃 爷爷说 说那很平和
Um, w-w-well, Granddad said it was, uh, peaceful.

943
01:09:11,570 --> 01:09:13,270
平和？
Peaceful?

944
01:09:13,290 --> 01:09:16,190
他自尽了 上吊的
He killed himself. Hung himself.

945
01:09:16,210 --> 01:09:19,890
他老婆跟个刚满十八的小伙子私奔了
His wife, you see, she ran off with this younger man, barely old enough to vote.

946
01:09:19,910 --> 01:09:23,460
她自己都四十多了 你怎么看？
And she was in her 40s. What do you think of that?

947
01:09:23,480 --> 01:09:25,030
-天哪 -对 可不是
-Wow. -Damn right, wow.

948
01:09:25,050 --> 01:09:28,880
我还听说...
And then, I heard that...

949
01:09:33,020 --> 01:09:36,180
学校那边有什么新鲜事？
What's happening at school?

950
01:09:36,200 --> 01:09:38,470
谁和谁在亲亲啦？
Who's smooching who?

951
01:09:38,500 --> 01:09:43,780
放心说吧 无人能闻得见 我只多留片刻
"Talk honestly, for no one else hears you and I stay only a minute longer."

952
01:09:43,800 --> 01:09:46,790
我是否自相矛盾？
"Do I contradict myself?

953
01:09:46,810 --> 01:09:51,570
好吧 那我就自相矛盾
"Very well then, I contradict myself,"

954
01:09:51,590 --> 01:09:56,010
我心疆无限 我包罗万象
"I am large. I contain multitudes."

955
01:09:56,030 --> 01:09:58,320
六年级的最后一堂课上
On the last day of sixth grade,

956
01:09:58,340 --> 01:10:04,540
那位小清新气息 管不住课堂的理查兹老师
Miss Richards, a sweet, hippie-dippyish young woman who had no command of discipline

957
01:10:04,560 --> 01:10:09,420
怕是很快就要被劝退
and would probably not last long in the public education system,

958
01:10:09,440 --> 01:10:17,770
还是在查克班上照念惠特曼《自我之歌》的诗
tried to recite for Chuck's class some verse of Walt Whitman's "Song of Myself."

959
01:10:17,790 --> 01:10:21,260
若最初寻我不得 莫失信心
"Failing to fetch me at first keep encouraged.

960
01:10:21,280 --> 01:10:25,440
错过此处 再觅它方
Missing me one place, search another."

961
01:10:37,330 --> 01:10:40,140
这节课还算顺利 对吧？
That went well, don't you think?

962
01:10:40,160 --> 01:10:43,830
嗯 让您为难了
Yeah, I'm, I'm sorry about that.

963
01:10:44,390 --> 01:10:54,380
惠特曼那句“我心疆无限 我包罗万象”是啥意思？
What does he mean when he says, "I am large, I contain multitudes"?

964
01:10:54,400 --> 01:10:56,730
你觉得他想表达什么？
What do you think he means?

965
01:10:56,750 --> 01:10:59,090
包罗他认识的所有人
All the people he knows.

966
01:10:59,110 --> 01:11:00,520
对
Yes.

967
01:11:00,880 --> 01:11:04,050
但也许不止于此
But maybe he means even more.

968
01:11:04,080 --> 01:11:07,870
来 过来
Here. Come here.

969
01:11:09,320 --> 01:11:11,780
我的两手之间 那里有什么？
What's in there? Between my hands?

970
01:11:11,810 --> 01:11:13,570
我头
My brain.

971
01:11:13,590 --> 01:11:16,790
不 不是这个意思
No, um, that's not exactly what I mean.

972
01:11:16,810 --> 01:11:22,010
我是说 在我两手之间 里面装的是什么
What's in there? Right between my hands right now.

973
01:11:22,030 --> 01:11:23,180
我不知道
I don't know.

974
01:11:23,200 --> 01:11:26,260
里面有你认识的所有人吗？
All the people you know?

975
01:11:26,280 --> 01:11:27,800
有吧
I guess.

976
01:11:27,820 --> 01:11:31,780
就只有你认识的人吗？
Just the people you know?

977
01:11:31,800 --> 01:11:36,460
里面是你见过的记住的一切
Everything you see. Everything you know.

978
01:11:36,480 --> 01:11:38,570
是整个世界 查克
The world, Chuck.

979
01:11:38,590 --> 01:11:41,290
天上的飞机 地上的井盖
Planes in the sky. Manhole covers in the street.

980
01:11:41,310 --> 01:11:44,430
年复一年 你脑海中的世界
Every year that you live, that world inside your head

981
01:11:44,450 --> 01:11:49,130
会越来越大 越鲜明 越丰富 越复杂
will get bigger and brighter and more detailed and complex.

982
01:11:49,150 --> 01:11:52,780
你会在脑海中构建城市 国家 大陆
You will build cities and countries and continents,

983
01:11:52,800 --> 01:11:57,650
并用真实和想象的人去充实那里
and you will fill them with people and faces, real and imagined.

984
01:11:57,670 --> 01:12:00,070
明白了吗？
Do you understand?

985
01:12:00,090 --> 01:12:01,790
别就此止步
Don't stop there.

986
01:12:01,810 --> 01:12:06,240
把你见过的 认识的
You fill the whole thing with everyone you ever meet,

987
01:12:06,270 --> 01:12:11,750
甚至想象的每个人都给装进去
everyone you ever know, everyone you ever just imagine.

988
01:12:11,780 --> 01:12:14,760
它就变成了个小宇宙
It'll be a universe.

989
01:12:14,780 --> 01:12:20,330
整个宇宙就在我两手之间
A whole universe right between my hands.

990
01:12:20,350 --> 01:12:25,850
你能包罗万象
You contain multitudes.

991
01:12:26,180 --> 01:12:27,960
那
So...

992
01:12:29,010 --> 01:12:33,260
那个宇宙会怎样 要是有人
what happens to that universe if someone...

993
01:12:33,280 --> 01:12:35,440
比如说
I don't know,

994
01:12:35,460 --> 01:12:41,790
在冰面上打滑 冲下高架桥 或者
hits a patch of ice and goes off an overpass or...

995
01:12:41,940 --> 01:12:44,790
别太纠结这些
Don't worry too much about those things.

996
01:12:44,810 --> 01:12:50,320
只要记住 你包罗万象 查克
Just remember that you contain multitudes, Chuck.

997
01:12:50,340 --> 01:12:53,770
这多棒啊
Isn't that wonderful?

998
01:12:54,170 --> 01:12:56,450
好了 就这样 你真是个好孩子
Now, go on. You were such a good boy.

999
01:12:56,480 --> 01:13:00,410
能教你我很开心
I've really enjoyed having you in class.

1000
01:13:20,150 --> 01:13:24,440
查克暑假本来过得挺好 直到八月
Chuck did enjoy his summer until August,

1001
01:13:24,460 --> 01:13:27,690
他阿奶去世了
when Bubbie died.

1002
01:13:30,400 --> 01:13:33,400
事情发生在街角的便利店里
It happened at the grocery store down the street,

1003
01:13:33,430 --> 01:13:37,150
公开场合 有点不太体面
in public, which was a little undignified,

1004
01:13:37,170 --> 01:13:41,250
至少这种死法能让人安心地说...
but at least it was the kind of death where people can safely say...

1005
01:13:41,280 --> 01:13:44,070
幸好她一生没受什么罪
Thank God she didn't suffer.

1006
01:13:44,090 --> 01:13:45,560
至于那句...
The other standby...

1007
01:13:45,580 --> 01:13:47,390
她一生又长又圆满
She had a long, full life.

1008
01:13:47,410 --> 01:13:50,160
就说不准了
...was more of a gray area.

1009
01:13:50,180 --> 01:13:54,620
毕竟她才六十多岁
Sarah Krantz had yet to reach her mid-60s.

1010
01:13:57,030 --> 01:14:03,720
又一次 家里再次陷入彻底的悲伤
Once more, the house on Pilchard Street was one of unadulterated sadness.

1011
01:14:04,110 --> 01:14:07,800
阿尔比戴上了黑纱 越发消瘦
Albie wore his mourning band, and lost weight,

1012
01:14:07,830 --> 01:14:10,220
也不再讲笑话了
and stopped telling his jokes

1013
01:14:10,240 --> 01:14:14,930
比他实际七十岁还显老
and began to look older than his 70 years.

1014
01:14:21,350 --> 01:14:24,370
-就买这点？ -嗯
-That's it? -Yeah.

1015
01:14:24,390 --> 01:14:26,980
一块七毛五
Buck 75.

1016
01:14:28,390 --> 01:14:35,340
几周前来的那个女士 就是后来去世的那位
Um, that lady who was in here a few weeks ago, the one who died.

1017
01:14:35,360 --> 01:14:38,780
事情发生在哪儿？
Where was she when it happened?

1018
01:14:38,800 --> 01:14:42,380
小朋友 这话题有点吓人
That's a little creepy, kid.

1019
01:14:42,410 --> 01:14:45,430
她是我奶奶
She was my grandma.

1020
01:14:46,020 --> 01:14:48,060
她当时想拿面包
She was getting a loaf of bread.

1021
01:14:48,080 --> 01:14:52,620
结果把整排货架都拽倒砸她身上了
Pulled down almost everything on the shelf when she collapsed.

1022
01:14:52,640 --> 01:14:57,250
要是我说多了 你别介意
I'm sorry if that's too much information.

1023
01:14:57,770 --> 01:14:59,630
没事
Nah.

1024
01:15:00,510 --> 01:15:03,720
我早知道了
I already knew that.

1025
01:15:57,440 --> 01:16:00,160
-别！ -啥？
-No! -What?!

1026
01:16:00,180 --> 01:16:05,830
-走开 快走开 -等下
-Get away from there! You get away from there. -What? Hey, hey!

1027
01:16:27,090 --> 01:16:30,070
把锁给我
Give me that.

1028
01:16:30,380 --> 01:16:32,930
给我 给我
Give it to me. Give it to me.

1029
01:16:32,950 --> 01:16:36,520
