I don't, I don't know.

1208
01:28:42,380 --> 01:28:44,520
鞋子怪怪的
My shoes feel all funny,

1209
01:28:44,550 --> 01:28:48,470
我 我脚扭了
and... I hurt my leg.

1210
01:28:48,820 --> 01:28:51,670
哦 你脚扭了？
Oh, you hurt your leg?

1211
01:28:51,690 --> 01:28:53,020
嗯
Yeah.

1212
01:28:53,210 --> 01:28:56,230
真替你可惜
I'm sorry to hear that.

1213
01:28:56,350 --> 01:28:57,980
你一个人来的？
So, you came stag, huh?

1214
01:28:58,000 --> 01:29:00,570
-啥？ -没有舞伴？
-Hmm? -No date.

1215
01:29:00,600 --> 01:29:02,290
没 我
Nah, I...

1216
01:29:02,310 --> 01:29:07,950
情况会变的 相信我 迟早会变 再等等
That'll change. Believe me, it'll change. Just give it some time.

1217
01:29:07,970 --> 01:29:09,770
舞池里这些...
None of this, none of...

1218
01:29:09,790 --> 01:29:12,650
舞池里这些都不重要
None of that out there really means anything.

1219
01:29:12,670 --> 01:29:18,440
跳得怎样 都只是热身和演习 别把它当真
It's all just, just a scrimmage. Just a practice.

1220
01:29:19,500 --> 01:29:21,830
嘿 这首正好 来跳吧
Hey, this is perfect. Come on.

1221
01:29:21,850 --> 01:29:24,180
不行 我...
Nah, I'm still, uh...

1222
01:29:24,200 --> 01:29:25,750
我脚还怪怪的
My leg's still wonky.

1223
01:29:25,780 --> 01:29:28,660
查克 得了吧 让我们炸翻全场
Chuck, come on. We're gonna blow the roof off.

1224
01:29:28,680 --> 01:29:30,370
对不起
I'm sorry.

1225
01:29:30,900 --> 01:29:33,270
真的很痛
It really hurts.

1226
01:29:46,920 --> 01:29:52,690
我从八岁就开始跳舞 又教体育
You know, I've been dancing since I was eight, and I teach PE,

1227
01:29:52,710 --> 01:29:55,120
看过不少孩子受伤后的样子
and I've seen when my kids get hurt.

1228
01:29:55,140 --> 01:29:57,630
他们走路都不一样了
I see how their walk changes.

1229
01:29:57,660 --> 01:29:59,570
站姿也怪
I see how their posture changes.

1230
01:29:59,600 --> 01:30:02,720
说句实话 在我看来
And don't mind me saying, but you look...

1231
01:30:03,250 --> 01:30:06,400
查克 你看上去好好的
Well, you look fine to me, Chuck.

1232
01:30:06,420 --> 01:30:11,060
我没逼你非得跟她跳 决定权在你
I'm not saying that you have to dance with the girl. It's up to you.

1233
01:30:11,090 --> 01:30:16,200
我只想说 不管跳不跳 别说谎
 I'm just saying dance or no dance, you don't have to lie.

1234
01:30:16,220 --> 01:30:19,650
跟她实话实说
Tell her the truth.

1235
01:30:20,470 --> 01:30:23,700
她会理解的
She can take it.

1236
01:31:35,980 --> 01:31:39,720
-准备好了吗？ -嗯 来跳吧
-You ready? -Yeah. Let's do it.

1237
01:33:59,080 --> 01:34:05,520
再跳一遍！再跳一遍！
One more time! One more time!

1238
01:34:05,870 --> 01:34:13,420
他们年纪虽小 却足够聪明知道何时收场
They may have been young, but they were smart enough to know when to quit.

1239
01:34:18,930 --> 01:34:20,390
谢谢大家
Thank you, guys.

1240
01:34:20,410 --> 01:34:25,700
在他39岁因脑瘤早逝前六个月
Six months before he died of a brain tumor at the unfair age of 39,

1241
01:34:25,720 --> 01:34:29,440
趁头脑还算清楚
and while his mind was still working, mostly,

1242
01:34:29,460 --> 01:34:35,750
他跟妻子珍妮坦白了手背上疤的来历
Chuck told his wife the truth about the scar on the back of his hand.

1243
01:34:35,770 --> 01:34:37,620
最开始交往时
When they'd first started dating,

1244
01:34:37,640 --> 01:34:41,250
他说这疤是那晚舞会后
he told her he'd gotten it from a boy named Doug Wentworth,

1245
01:34:41,270 --> 01:34:46,150
舞伴凯特的男友温特沃斯因为吃醋
who was pissed about him dancing with his girlfriend at a middle school formal

1246
01:34:46,170 --> 01:34:49,530
把他推到围栏上铁丝划的
and pushed him into a chain link fence outside the gym.

1247
01:34:49,550 --> 01:34:52,710
这疤我没说真话
I lied about that, though.

1248
01:34:54,050 --> 01:34:59,680
哇 你还是这么神秘
Oh, my. A man of secrets, even still.

1249
01:35:01,060 --> 01:35:02,870
亲爱的 怎么弄的？
What happened, love?

1250
01:35:02,890 --> 01:35:05,560
那晚舞跳完
When our fabulous dance was over, I...

1251
01:35:05,580 --> 01:35:08,740
我全身又汗又热
I was sweaty and I was so hot.

1252
01:35:08,760 --> 01:35:10,920
脸都热得通红
I-I felt like my cheeks were gonna catch fire.

1253
01:35:10,950 --> 01:35:12,190
跳的太好了
You were great.

1254
01:35:12,220 --> 01:35:14,870
-谢谢 -真是个大明星啊
-Thank you. -What a star.

1255
01:35:14,900 --> 01:35:18,490
我那时只想逃离灯光
All I wanted in that moment was just darkness,

1256
01:35:18,510 --> 01:35:24,950
吹吹凉风 一个人呆会儿
cool air, and to be by myself.

1257
01:35:27,000 --> 01:35:30,720
那晚天空繁星闪烁
There were millions of stars that night.

1258
01:35:30,740 --> 01:35:32,590
千万星辰
Millions of them.

1259
01:35:32,610 --> 01:35:35,330
千层万叠
And millions more behind them.

1260
01:35:35,350 --> 01:35:40,290
也许 嗯 它们只是天文数字
And sure, m-may... Yeah, maybe they were just math.

1261
01:35:40,310 --> 01:35:42,920
却好像在翩翩起舞
But they also danced.

1262
01:35:42,940 --> 01:35:47,380
我知道 因为那一瞬我看见了
I know 'cause I saw one of them.

1263
01:35:47,880 --> 01:35:51,520
我那时想 宇宙边疆无限
And I remember thinking, the universe is large

1264
01:35:51,540 --> 01:35:54,060
宇宙包罗万象
and, and it contains multitudes,

1265
01:35:54,090 --> 01:35:58,460
也包含了我
but it-it also contains me.

1266
01:35:58,590 --> 01:36:04,670
而在那一刻 我真觉得自己很精彩
And in this moment...I am wonderful.

1267
01:36:04,690 --> 01:36:07,920
我理应拥有这份精彩
And I have a right to be wonderful.

1268
01:36:07,950 --> 01:36:09,870
啊
Oh!

1269
01:36:12,780 --> 01:36:16,160
干嘛为这事撒谎 小傻瓜
Why lie about that, silly?

1270
01:36:16,180 --> 01:36:20,070
你真是个奇妙的存在 亲爱的
You're a strange wonder, my dear.

1271
01:36:20,090 --> 01:36:26,990
他没再多说 因为那道疤另有深意
He doesn't offer more because the scar was important for another reason.

1272
01:36:27,010 --> 01:36:30,170
是他讲不完的故事的一环
It was part of a story he couldn't tell,

1273
01:36:30,190 --> 01:36:35,180
其中有他长大的那幢维多利亚老宅
even though there was now an apartment building on the site of the Victorian house

1274
01:36:35,200 --> 01:36:38,740
尽管早拆了盖楼了
where he had done most of his growing up.

1275
01:36:38,760 --> 01:36:42,960
那幢闹鬼的维多利亚老宅
The haunted Victorian house.

1276
01:36:42,990 --> 01:36:44,860
不知道
No reason.

1277
01:36:45,820 --> 01:36:48,100
就是心血来潮吧
Funny thinking, I guess.

1278
01:36:48,120 --> 01:36:52,630
这疤意义非凡 他也尽力讲得加料
The scar meant more, so he had made it more.

1279
01:36:52,650 --> 01:36:57,070
可讲得总没有它真正的意义深
He just couldn't make it as much more as it really was.

1280
01:36:57,090 --> 01:36:59,290
讲得还有点糊涂
That made little sense.

1281
01:36:59,320 --> 01:37:03,690
但随着脑癌细胞的疯狂进攻
But as the glioblastoma continued its blitzkrieg,

1282
01:37:03,710 --> 01:37:09,910
他那快散架的大脑最多也只能讲到这样
it was the best his disintegrating mind could manage.

1283
01:37:39,860 --> 01:37:43,640
查克的爷爷 他的阿爷
Chuck's grandpa, his Zaydee,

1284
01:37:43,660 --> 01:37:49,470
在那场秋季舞会五年后 因心脏病发作去世
died of a heart attack five years after the Fall Fling dance.

1285
01:37:49,490 --> 01:37:51,920
事发时查克读高二
Chuck was a junior in high school

1286
01:37:51,940 --> 01:37:53,730
是乐队主唱
singing in a band and

1287
01:37:53,760 --> 01:37:57,980
正在台上像摇滚巨星一样跳得带劲儿
dancing like Jagger during the instrumental breaks.

1288
01:37:58,000 --> 01:38:01,220
他自己都安排妥当了
He made all the arrangements himself.

1289
01:38:01,240 --> 01:38:03,120
几周前
Came in a few weeks ago

1290
01:38:03,140 --> 01:38:05,730
还特地来馆里再确认一遍
just to make sure everything was to the letter,

1291
01:38:05,750 --> 01:38:08,010
我还纳闷呢
which I thought was strange.

1292
01:38:08,310 --> 01:38:10,390
很少有人这么上心
Not many people bother to do that.

1293
01:38:10,410 --> 01:38:15,010
大多数人只来一趟定好流程
Most people, they come here once to set it all up.

1294
01:38:15,250 --> 01:38:18,410
办好手续就不再来了
They aren't anxious to come back again.

1295
01:38:18,430 --> 01:38:25,070
再见到那人 都是穿着体面衣服躺那儿 懂吧
Next time I see 'em, they're in their Sunday best, if you get me.

1296
01:38:25,090 --> 01:38:29,180
他人特好 也是我多年的好友
He was a great man and a good friend.

1297
01:38:29,670 --> 01:38:32,750
他为我们做账整整二十三年了
He's been doing our books for 23 years

1298
01:38:32,780 --> 01:38:38,040
账做得稳 多次税务检查都帮我们顺利过关
and saved our skin more than once when the tax man was coming.

1299
01:38:38,810 --> 01:38:41,340
要现在给你结账吗？
So, do I owe you any money?

1300
01:38:41,370 --> 01:38:42,940
一分都不用
Not a penny.

1301
01:38:42,960 --> 01:38:48,700
他那次来就把钱全给结清了
He took care of that too. Settled his tab that same visit.

1302
01:38:48,750 --> 01:38:50,500
听我说
You know...

1303
01:38:50,980 --> 01:38:53,050
最离奇的是
the strangest thing.

1304
01:38:53,070 --> 01:38:56,400
这事儿很怪 可别觉得我扯
And this will sound strange, so bear with me.

1305
01:38:56,420 --> 01:38:58,050
说来话长
See,

1306
01:38:58,050 --> 01:39:03,110
年轻时我曾想当电视上天气预报员
I, uh, dreamed of being a television weatherman in my salad days

1307
01:39:03,130 --> 01:39:05,850
也许能成全国台的
with maybe one of the networks.

1308
01:39:05,870 --> 01:39:07,980
最终没成
Wasn't in the cards for me.

1309
01:39:08,310 --> 01:39:13,120
倒是去地方台待过一个夏天
But I did spend a summer at WKNB.

1310
01:39:13,140 --> 01:39:17,950
在那儿 有个同事号称能
Well, there was a guy at KNB who they said

1311
01:39:17,970 --> 01:39:23,930
不用雷达就能提前两周感知风暴
could feel a storm coming two solid weeks away without the radar.

1312
01:39:23,960 --> 01:39:25,690
有第六感
Had a sixth sense.

1313
01:39:25,720 --> 01:39:28,040
简直了
Damnedest thing I ever saw.

1314
01:39:28,060 --> 01:39:30,350
他会露出一种神情
Uh, used to make this face,

1315
01:39:30,370 --> 01:39:33,830
当别人说要出远门
this face when people talked about their travel plans,

1316
01:39:33,850 --> 01:39:35,920
然后他洞察出什么后
if he knew something they didn't.

1317
01:39:35,940 --> 01:39:40,930
那神情不笑不乐
Not... not a smile, per se. No joy in it.

1318
01:39:40,950 --> 01:39:45,370
就一脸 我全知道的样子
Just a... knowing.

1319
01:39:45,390 --> 01:39:48,310
我管那叫 预报员天眼
"Weatherman Stare," I called it.

1320
01:39:48,340 --> 01:39:51,010
我可没那本事
And I didn't have it, not me.

1321
01:39:51,040 --> 01:39:55,890
所以我在这行 而不是那行
So, I'm here, not there.

1322
01:39:56,130 --> 01:40:01,600
你爷爷来时也带着同样的神情
Your granddad had that same face when he was in here.

1323
01:40:01,620 --> 01:40:05,730
像是 他早料到要下雨
Like... he knew it was gonna rain.

1324
01:40:05,750 --> 01:40:10,480
而我只是个卖他伞的人
And I was just a guy selling him an umbrella.

1325
01:40:10,500 --> 01:40:12,770
那就是预报员天眼
Weatherman Stare.

1326
01:40:12,800 --> 01:40:15,370
我敢打包票
I'm sure of it.

1327
01:40:15,850 --> 01:40:18,110
太离谱了
The strangest thing.

1328
01:40:19,200 --> 01:40:21,450
爷爷阿尔比把一切家当都留给了他
Albie left him everything.

1329
01:40:21,470 --> 01:40:25,090
这足够支付他的大学学费
More than enough to pay for his college education.

1330
01:40:25,110 --> 01:40:28,450
再后来 他把那幢维多利亚老宅卖了
And later on, the sale of the Victorian

1331
01:40:28,470 --> 01:40:30,430
用这笔钱买了
paid for the house he and Ginny moved into

1332
01:40:30,460 --> 01:40:35,460
和他妻子珍妮度蜜月后住的新家
after their honeymoon in the Catskills.

1333
01:40:35,480 --> 01:40:41,250
他铁了心不去奥马哈和外公外婆一起住
He flatly refused to move to Omaha to live with his mother's parents.

1334
01:40:41,270 --> 01:40:43,160
-听着 我真的很爱你们... -他这样说
-Look, I love you guys... -He said.

1335
01:40:43,180 --> 01:40:46,630
...但我在这里长大的 也想在这待到上大学
...but this is where I grew up and want to stay till college.

1336
01:40:46,660 --> 01:40:48,690
我都17了 不是小孩子了
I'm 17. I'm not a baby.

1337
01:40:48,710 --> 01:40:54,650
于是 早已退休的老两口 住进那幢维多利亚老宅
So, they, both long retired, came to him and stayed in the Victorian

1338
01:40:54,670 --> 01:40:57,520
陪查克二十多个月
for the 20-odd months before Chuck went off

1339
01:40:57,540 --> 01:41:01,840
直到他去伊利诺伊大学
to the University of Illinois.

1340
01:41:01,920 --> 01:41:06,600
可他们没赶上参加葬礼
They weren't able to be there for the funeral, however.

1341
01:41:06,630 --> 01:41:09,280
葬礼办得迅速利落 正如阿尔比所愿
It happened fast, as Albie had wanted,

1342
01:41:09,300 --> 01:41:14,260
他外公外婆在奥马哈还有一些事要收尾
and his mom's folks had loose ends to tie up in Omaha.

1343
01:41:14,290 --> 01:41:17,890
说实话 查克并不怎么想他们
Chuck didn't really miss them, if he was honest.

1344
01:41:17,910 --> 01:41:25,750
他跟他阿爷一样 最讨厌瞎折腾 也受不了人多
His Zaydee hated a fuss almost as much as he hated a crowd.

1345
01:41:26,650 --> 01:41:29,470
他们来的前一天
A day before they were scheduled to arrive,

1346
01:41:29,490 --> 01:41:31,840
查克才拆开
Chuck finally opened the envelope

1347
01:41:31,870 --> 01:41:36,120
放玄关桌上的那大信封
that had been sitting on the table in the front hall.

1348
01:41:36,140 --> 01:41:38,870
信封是来自山姆·亚伯勒
It was from Sam Yarborough,

1349
01:41:38,890 --> 01:41:42,960
亚伯勒殡仪馆的老板兼首席殡葬师
owner and chief undertaker at Yarborough Funeral Home,

1350
01:41:42,980 --> 01:41:49,700
里面装着阿尔比·克兰兹的个人物品
and inside were Albie Krantz's personal effects.

1351
01:43:43,960 --> 01:43:48,170
在这屋里 查克爷爷见过杰弗里家那男孩
In this room, Chuck's grandpa had seen the Jefferies boy,

1352
01:43:48,190 --> 01:43:51,840
被车撞得血肉模糊
body broken by the car.

1353
01:43:51,870 --> 01:43:56,230
他见过亨利·彼得森吊在天花板上
He'd seen Henry Peterson hanging from the ceiling.

1354
01:43:56,250 --> 01:43:59,510
他还见过他妻子躺在地上断了气
He'd seen his own wife lying dead.

1355
01:43:59,530 --> 01:44:01,930
查克想
And likely, Chuck supposed,

1356
01:44:01,950 --> 01:44:05,970
也许就在那晚偷他钥匙的时候
perhaps the night Chuck had stolen his keys,

1357
01:44:05,990 --> 01:44:10,330
阿尔比还看见自己摔倒在地
Albie had even seen himself crumpled to the floor,

1358
01:44:10,350 --> 01:44:13,770
死死抓着胳膊
still clutching his upper arm.

1359
01:44:13,790 --> 01:44:17,550
“这就是等待”他爷爷曾说
"It's the waiting," he'd said.

1360
01:44:17,570 --> 01:44:20,640
“这是最难熬的”
"That's the hard part."

1361
01:44:20,660 --> 01:44:24,950
现在轮到查克自己的煎熬了
Now Chuck's own waiting would begin.

1362
01:44:24,970 --> 01:44:27,910
到底要等多久？
How long would that wait be?

1363
01:44:27,930 --> 01:44:33,860
病床上那个人到底多少岁？
Exactly how old was the man in the hospital bed?

1364
01:44:36,980 --> 01:44:42,180
看不见的监护仪发出最后一声“哔”
There was a final bip from the unseen monitor

1365
01:44:42,200 --> 01:44:45,600
然后也随之消失
and then that was gone too.

1366
01:44:46,990 --> 01:44:52,630
不像电影里那样慢慢淡去
The man did not fade, as ghostly apparitions did in the movies.

1367
01:44:52,650 --> 01:44:55,280
就直接不见了
He was just gone.

1368
01:44:55,300 --> 01:45:00,080
仿佛从未出现过
Insisting he had never been there in the first place.

1369
01:45:00,530 --> 01:45:02,930
-那不可能... -查克想
-He wasn't... -Chuck thinks.

1370
01:45:02,950 --> 01:45:05,860
...我偏不信
...and I will insist he wasn't.

1371
01:45:05,880 --> 01:45:11,520
我会痛痛快快地活 直到最后一刻
And I will live my life until my life runs out.

1372
01:45:11,540 --> 01:45:14,280
我很精彩
I am wonderful.

1373
01:45:14,850 --> 01:45:18,380
我配得上这份精彩
I deserve to be wonderful.

1374
01:45:19,240 --> 01:45:22,620
我包罗万象
And I contain multitudes.

1375
01:45:48,090 --> 01:45:50,680
